## Google debuts an updated Gemini 2.5 Pro AI model ahead of I/O  

Google has introduced the **Gemini 2.5 Pro Preview (I/O edition)**, an upgraded version of its flagship AI model, which the company says outperforms several widely-used benchmarks. The new model is now accessible via the Gemini API, Vertex AI, and AI Studio platforms, though pricing details remain unspecified.  

### Why It Matters  

Google’s latest update to **Gemini 2.5 Pro** signals its continued push to lead in the competitive AI landscape, particularly ahead of its I/O developer conference. By emphasizing benchmark dominance, Google aims to attract developers and enterprises looking for cutting-edge AI capabilities. The availability across multiple platforms suggests a strategic move to expand adoption, reinforcing its position against rivals like OpenAI and Anthropic.
